<P>This &s;atisfied me in Part, but I &s;ound Means after his, to enquire, who&s;e particular Troop it was that the Gentlemen that were here, belong'd to; and with that, heard, they would all be at <HI>Paris</HI> the Week after.</P>
<P>Two Days after this, we return'd for <HI>Paris,</HI> when I $ook Occa&s;ion to &s;peak to my Lord, that I heard the <HI>$$n. d'arms</HI> were to be in the City the next Week, and that I &s;hould be charm'd with &s;eeing them march, if they came in a Body: He was &s;o obliging in &s;uch Things, that I need but ju&s;t name a Thing of that Kind, and it was done; &s;o he order'd his Gentleman (I &s;hou'd now $all him <HI>Amy</HI>'s <HI>Gentleman)</HI> to get me a Place in a cer|tain Hou&s;e, where I might &s;ee them march.</P>
<P>As he did not appear with me on this Occa&s;ion, &s;o I $Word$ the Liberty of taking my Woman <HI>Amy</HI> with me; and &s;tood where we were very well accommodated for $$e Ob&s;ervation which I was to make: I told <HI>Amy</HI> what $had &s;een, and &s;he was as forward to make the Di&s;|$overy, as I was to have her, and almo&s;t as much &s;ur|$riz'd at the Thing it&s;elf; in a Word, the <HI>Gens d'arms</HI> $ter'd the City, as was expected, and made a mo&s;t $orious Show indeed, being new-cloath'd and arm'd, $d being to have their Standards ble&s;s'd by the Arch|$&s;hop of <HI>Paris:</HI> on this Occa&s;ion, they indeed look'd $$y gay; and as they march'd very lei&s;urely, I had $ime to take as critical a View, and make as nice a $arch among them, as I pleas'd: Here in a particular $$k, eminent for one mon&s;trous &s;iz'd Man on the Right; $$e, I &s;ay, I &s;aw my Gentleman again, and a very $and&s;ome jolly Fellow he was, as any in the Troop, $o' not &s;o mon&s;trous large as that great one I &s;peak of, $o it &s;eems was however, a Gentleman of a good $$mily in <HI>Ga&s;cogne,</HI> and was call'd the <HI>Giant of Ga&s;|$$e.</HI></P>
<P>It was a Kind of a good Fortune to us, among the $er Circum&s;tances of it, that &s;omething caus'd the $$oops to Halt in their March, a little before that par|$lar Rank came right-again&s;t that Window which I $d in, &s;o that then we had Occa&s;ion to take our full
